<h5 id="subject_1129285">
<a href="?PHPSESSID=608b062285b07a8dd1e4c54d0838ba14&amp;topic=127222.msg1129285#msg1129285" rel="nofollow">Re: 【DW12th】神秘博士TRPG 第三章：我能对抗怪物，但不能对抗物理</a>
</h5>
<div class="zh_convert" style="float:right;display:none">
[<a href="javascript:convertToTraditional(document.getElementById('msg_1129285'));undefined;">繁</a>
<a href="javascript:convertToSimplified (document.getElementById('msg_1129285'));undefined;">简</a>]</div>
<div class="smalltext">&#171; <strong>回帖 #6 于:</strong> 2021-08-13, 周五 14:46:04 &#187;</div>
<div id="msg_1129285_quick_mod"></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="post">
<div class="inner" id="msg_1129285"><strong><span style="color: orange;" class="bbc_color"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" class="bbc_size">OPTIONAL RULE: THE DRAMA DIE<br>可选规则：戏剧性骰子</span></span></strong><br><br>如果计算成功等级拖慢了游戏节奏，主持人可能会弃用此规则，只计算简单的成功或失败。或者，如果你还是喜欢详细多样的结果，但不想计算难度值和掷骰结果的差值，你可以再掷一个额外的骰子来随机决定成败。“戏剧性骰子”可以是一个单独的、不同颜色的骰子，与其他骰子一起掷出，以决定成功等级。<br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i> </i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">If calculating the levels of success slows your game down, the Gamemaster may decide to discard them and stick with a simple Success or Failure. Alternatively, if you’d still like the detailed and varied result without having to work out the difference between the Difficulty and the Result, you could roll an additional die to generate the degree of success randomly. A “drama die” could be a single, different-coloured die that is rolled with the other dice that can determine the degree of success.</div></div></div><br>1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Success (Yes, But...)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Failure (No, But...)<br>2-5&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Good (Yes)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Bad (No)<br>6&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Fantastic (Yes, And...)&nbsp; Disastrous (No, And...)<br><br><br>这可能有点随机，但它确实能加快游戏速度，并可能给出更夸张的、角色通常达不到的成功水平。<br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i> </i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">It can be a little random, but it does speed things up and may allow a more extreme level of success that may normally be out of reach to the character.</div></div></div><br><span style="color: purple;" class="bbc_color"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" class="bbc_size"><strong>DAMAGE<br>伤害</strong></span></span><br><br>你可能已经注意到，成败表还提到了伤害以及掷骰结果怎样影响它。所有武器和导致受伤的情况都有固定的伤害值。这个数字根据掷骰（你射击的精准度，或闪避的敏捷程度）来调整。减半或乘以1.5倍的计算可能得出一半或四分之一值——对此向下取整，除非数值为零。既然伤害已经以某种形式产生，那么最低的值必须为1。我们稍后将介绍伤害和冲突（见85页）。<br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i> </i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">You’ll have noticed that the Success Tables also mention damage and how it is affected depending upon how well or how badly you’ve rolled. All weapons or forms of injury have a fixed damage. This number is modified depending on the roll (either how well you shot at someone, or how badly you dodged the harm). Halving, or multiplying the damage by 1.5 (one and a half times), may result in half or quarter numbers – always round down to the nearest whole number, unless the number is zero (0). Damage has been done in some form, so the lowest it can be is one (1). We’ll discuss damage and conflict later (see pg.85).</div></div></div><br><strong><span style="color: purple;" class="bbc_color"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" class="bbc_size">USING STORY POINTS<br>使用故事点</span></span></strong><br><br>没有达到预期的结果吗？别担心，事情还没完蛋。如果把所有的成败等级想象成一个梯子，你可以花一个故事点向上移动一个“横档” ，也就是说，把Success变成Good，或者把Good变成Fantastic结果。<br><br>在一项至关重要的任务上惨败？你可以使用故事点来改变特别糟糕的结果，每花一个故事点上升一级。然而，以这种方式花费故事点最多只允许达到Success结果。更多关于花费故事点改变掷骰结果的规则见102页。<br><br>如果一个玩家的故事点很少，那么在剧情合理的情况下，可以反向操作将Success转化为Failure以重新获得故事点。游戏主持人拥有最终决定权，不应鼓励过于频繁地这样做，但这确实能稍微增加戏剧性，而且是为关键时刻储存故事点的好办法。更多关于奖励和花费故事点的规则见106页。<br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i> </i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">Didn’t do as well as hoped? Don’t worry, all is not lost. If you imagine all the levels of success and failure as a ladder, you can spend a Story Point to move up one ‘rung’, so to speak, turning a Success into a Good, or a Good into a Fantastic Result.<br><br>Failed miserably at a task that was vital? You can spend Story Points to recover from a particularly bad result, moving up a rung per Story Point. However, spending Story Points in this way does limit you to a highest level of just ‘Success’. More on spending Story Points to effect the outcome of a roll can be found on p.102.<br><br>If a player is low on Story Points and it suits the story, they can do the reverse and turn a Success into a Failure to regain Story Points. The Gamemaster has the final say, and doing this too often should not be encouraged, but it can stir things up a little and can be a good way to build up Story Points in times of need. More on awarding and spending Story Points can be found on pg.106.</div></div></div><br><strong><span style="color: orange;" class="bbc_color"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" class="bbc_size">THE SUCCESS TABLE LADDER<br>成功等级阶梯表</span></span></strong><br><br>9+ above&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Fantastic<br>4-8 above&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Good<br>0-3 above&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Success<br>1-3 below&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Failure<br>4-8 below&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bad<br>9+ below&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Disastrous!<br><br><strong><span style="color: purple;" class="bbc_color"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" class="bbc_size">COOPERATION<br>合作</span></span></strong><br><br>有时一项任务非常棘手或复杂，以至于角色不得不求助。人多力量大！一个具备所需技能的人将成为任务的领袖。其他人作为助手，如果有合适的技能来帮忙，则每人为领袖提供+2值。游戏主持人可以在任何情况下设置助手人数和有效技能的限制。<br><br><strong>举例：</strong>Vastra夫人今天过得很糟。她正在追捕一个雅贼，那人偷了有致命风险的外星科技物件；她既没时间也没耐心去和管家争论为什么她有权进入华丽的舞会厅，小偷已经躲在了那里。幸运的是，珍妮保持着冷静，她作为仆人向Vastra和管家提供“建议”，解释了夫人的邀请函是怎么被落下的。Vastra夫人要骰<em>气质</em>+<em>信服</em>技能，但因为珍妮的帮助，她掷出的点数额外+2。<br><br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i> </i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">Sometimes a task is so tricky or complicated, the characters are going to have to call in help. Many hands make light work! One person with the required skill will take the lead in the task. The helpers, if they have a suitable skill that could help, each add +2 to the leader’s attempt. The Gamemaster may put a limit on how many people can help in any given circumstance, and which skills are suitable to assist.<br><br><em><strong>Example:</strong> Madame Vastra is having a bad day. She is in pursuit of a gentleman thief who’s stolen a potentially lethal piece of alien technology from her; she doesn’t have the time or patience to argue with a steward as to why she should be allowed into the glamorous ball that the thief has ducked into. Fortunately, Jenny keeps a cool head and, in the role of servant, offers ‘suggestions’ to Vastra and the steward as to how her invitation has been misplaced. Madame Vastra rolls Presence + Convince skill, but because Jenny is helping she adds an extra +2 to her roll.<br></em><br></div></div></div><br><strong><span style="color: purple;" class="bbc_color"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" class="bbc_size">THIS MAY TAKE SOME TIME...<br>这可能会花点儿时间……</span></span></strong><br><br>另一种处理极为困难的任务的方法是慢慢来，花更长的时间对付它。主持人来决定角色完成任务需要多久。在这段时间结束时，正常掷骰看看是否成功。如果角色花了超出必需的时间，步步为营，相当仔细，就更有可能成功。花费两倍的时间会为掷骰提供+2点数，三倍时间+4，以此类推，直到+10的最大值。<br><br><strong>举例：</strong>博士正在试验一种混合化学药品，它能快速腐蚀戴立克金属。游戏主持人彼得知道博士很聪明，但还需要一段时间才能完成。彼得说：“你至少要花一个小时来混合和尝试配方才能做出有效药品。”扮演博士的玩家詹娜并不着急，这件事对玩家的成功至关重要。她决定花两个小时做实验，在这段时间结束后为博士的<em>才智</em> + <em>科学</em>掷骰获得+2的额外加值。<br><br>如果角色匆忙行事，则情况相反。欲速则不达！将行动时间减半，掷骰会受到-2的惩罚，以此类推，与多花时间得到奖励点数类似。<br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i> </i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">Another way to deal with incredibly hard tasks is to take your time and work at it over a longer period. The Gamemaster determines how long it is going to take for the character to complete the task. At the end of that time, make the roll as normal to see if you succeed. If the character spends longer than necessary on a task, taking their time and being extra careful, they are more likely to succeed. Taking twice as long adds a +2 bonus to the roll, three times as long adds +4, and so on up to a maximum bonus of +10.<br><br><em><strong>Example: </strong>The Doctor is experimenting with a mix of chemicals that will hopefully eat through Dalekanium in a very short time. The Gamemaster, Peter, knows the Doctor is brilliant, but it’s going to take a while to get this right. Peter says “It’s going to take at least an hour of mixing and trying formulas before you come close to a solution.” The Doctor’s player, Jenna, isn’t in a rush, and this is vital to the success of the players. She decides to spend two hours on the experiment and gains a +2 bonus on his Ingenuity + Science roll at the end of this time.</em><br><br>The opposite can be said if the character is rushing something. Trying to do things quickly can result in fumbling hands! Halving the time it would normally take to do something means the roll receives a -2 penalty, and so on, just like taking extra time.</div></div></div></div>
</div>
</div>
