<h5 id="subject_1129485">
<a href="?PHPSESSID=608b062285b07a8dd1e4c54d0838ba14&amp;topic=127222.msg1129485#msg1129485" rel="nofollow">Re: 【DW12th】神秘博士TRPG 第三章：我能对抗怪物，但不能对抗物理</a>
</h5>
<div class="zh_convert" style="float:right;display:none">
[<a href="javascript:convertToTraditional(document.getElementById('msg_1129485'));undefined;">繁</a>
<a href="javascript:convertToSimplified (document.getElementById('msg_1129485'));undefined;">简</a>]</div>
<div class="smalltext">&#171; <strong>回帖 #8 于:</strong> 2021-08-14, 周六 15:42:45 &#187;</div>
<div id="msg_1129485_quick_mod"></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="post">
<div class="inner" id="msg_1129485"><span style="color: navy;" class="bbc_color"><span style="font-size: 18pt;" class="bbc_size"><strong>EXTENDED CONFLICT<br>扩展冲突</strong></span></span><br><br>用一次掷骰解决小任务完全没问题，但如果形势更为紧张棘手，比如追逐或战斗，你可能想把行动分解成一系列多次掷骰。这不仅增加了紧张程度 ，也让每个玩家都能创造更多切身参与、令人兴奋的动作场面，而局势会随着每一次掷骰结果的好坏迅猛变化。<br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i> </i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">Resolving smaller tasks with just one dice roll is all well and good, but if the situation is more intense or involved, such as a chase or fight scene, you may wish to break the action down into a series of rolls. Not only does this add tension, but it also allows everyone to create more involved and exciting action scenes as the tables can turn quickly with a good or bad roll.</div></div></div><br><span style="font-size: 12pt;" class="bbc_size"><span style="color: purple;" class="bbc_color"><strong>SETTING THE SCENE<br>设置场景</strong></span></span><br><br>首先，游戏主持人为玩家“设置场景”，尽可能详细地描述位置，让每个人都知道自己的角色位于何处。如果角色们已经有了地图，主持人可以向玩家展示，或者粗略画个图，让每个人对这里有所了解。这并非必须的，只要每个人都知道他们在哪里，环境看起来怎样，以及任何重要的环境条件（下雨，起雾，黑暗，地面湿滑还是刺骨的寒冷？)。<br><br><strong>示例：</strong>珍妮被赛博人俘虏了。它们把昏迷的珍妮拖回了处理中心，博士和Vastra夫人在后追赶。他们远远地跟着赛博人，看到它们进入了大楼。两人从门里溜进去，四处张望。主持人在此设置场景。<br><br>主持人说：“你们进入了处理中心。周围是一堆黑暗的、冒着蒸汽的机器，呼啸而去，你们可以听到远处人们的哭喊声，他们正在被转化成更多的金属人。光线比较昏暗，低悬的聚光灯散布在走廊上, 四周挤满了机器。门开开关关，黄褐色的和红色的警示灯闪烁着，警报声使你们意识到，又一批不合适的人被烧为了灰烬。<br><br>机器的蒸汽使这个地方闷热不堪，但难掩此处邪恶意图的恐怖。在前方大约100米处，你们看到珍妮被两个赛博人拖着向前走。当你们注意到她的时候，看到她恢复了知觉，开始挣扎。”<br><br>游戏主持人设置了场景，让玩家对所处的地点、正在发生的事和面临的遭遇有所感受。玩家现在可以决定下一步的计划。<br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i> </i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">First, the Gamemaster ‘sets the scene’ for the players, describing the location as best they can so everyone knows where their characters physically are. If they have maps prepared, the Gamemaster can reveal these to the players, or draw a rough diagram so everyone can get a feel for the place. It’s not essential, just as long as everyone knows where they are, what it looks like and any important environmental conditions (is it raining, misty, dark, slippery or freezing cold?).<br><br><em><strong>Example:</strong> Jenny has been taken prisoner by the Cybermen. They’ve dragged her unconscious body back towards the processing centre, and the Doctor and Madame Vastra are giving chase. They follow the Cybermen from a distance, watching them enter the building. They sneak in through the doors and look around. It’s here that the Gamemaster sets the scene.<br><br>The Gamemaster says, “You enter the processing centre. Sprawled around you is a mass of dark and steaming machinery, whirring away, and you can hear the distant cries of people being converted into yet more of the metal men. It’s relatively dark, low- level spotlights are dotted around the corridors that squeeze between the machines. As doors open and close, amber and red warning lights flash, and sirens alert you to another batch of unsuitable candidates being incinerated.<br><br>The steam of the machinery makes the place hot and sticky, but nothing can disguise the horror of what this place is for. About 100 metres ahead of you, you can see Jenny being dragged along by two Cybermen. As you notice her, you see her regain consciousness and start to struggle.”<br><br>The Gamemaster has set the scene, given a feel for the location and what is going on, and the tone of the encounter to come. The players can now decide what they’re planning to do.</em></div></div></div><br><span style="color: purple;" class="bbc_color"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" class="bbc_size"><strong>ACTION ROUNDS<br>行动轮</strong></span></span><br><br>一旦主持人设置好场景，扩展冲突中的事件就会分解为行动轮。基本上，这表示每人都行动一次，在一个行动轮结束时，你按轮流顺序行动了一次，其他人也完成了自己的行动。你可以尝试在一轮中作出多个行动，但这比听起来要难。我们稍后会讲到。首先要做的是，决定每个人在这一轮计划做什么。<br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i> </i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">Once the Gamemaster has set the scene, the events in an Extended Conflict are broken down into action rounds. Basically this means that everyone gets a turn, and by the end of an action round you’ll have gone ‘round the table and everyone will have had their go. You can try to do more than one action in a round, but that’s harder than it sounds. We’ll cover that a little later. First thing to do is to decide what everyone’s planning on doing for that round.</div></div></div><br><strong><span style="color: purple;" class="bbc_color"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" class="bbc_size">INTENT<br>意图</span></span><br></strong><br>和一般的冲突一样，玩家们决定要做什么。他们可能会详细讨论计划，也可能只是边跑边喊：“你去那边，我来拦住他们！”游戏主持人决定对手在这一轮做什么，以及事情发生的顺序。<br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i> </i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">Just as in the normal Conflict, players decide what they will try to do. They may discuss their plan amongst themselves in detail, or it could be as simple as running while shouting, “You go that way, I’ll cut them off!” The Gamemaster decides what the adversaries will do in this round, and in what order things occur.</div></div></div><br><span style="color: purple;" class="bbc_color"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" class="bbc_size"><strong>WHO GOES FIRST?<br>谁先来？</strong></span></span><br><br>我们知道双方想做什么了，现在最大的问题是谁先开始，谁做什么事。每个角色一次只能采取一个行动，他们按照下述顺序行动，这取决于他们的行动类型。<br><br><strong>对话者：</strong>“不，不，不……等等！”<br>事实证明，在博士的冒险中，谈话或大喊大叫是非常重要的，言语比武器更强大（通常使用起来也更快）。这个地方可能会发生爆炸；你可能被人用枪指着；但在有人开枪或把你绑起来之前，你有机会先把话说完。<br><br><strong>移动者</strong>：“我说跑，你就跑……跑！”<br>跑动是常见的策略，当面对外星威胁时，人们通常会先跑起来。他们可能是在逃离什么东西，也可能只是跑进了事件发生地，总之是在移动，所以对话者之后就轮到他们了。即使你在试图悄无声息地潜入秘密基地，试图避开监控摄像头，你也是在从一处移动到另一处，所以你排在下一个。<br><br><strong>行动者：</strong>“我只要逆转这个电路的极性，事情就解决了！”<br>要做的事可以很复杂，比如重新布线电路，也可以很简单，例如开门。如果你不打算跑动，也不跟敌人交谈，你大概就是在计划做些事情来改变局势。<br><br><strong>战士：</strong>“开火！所有武器！”<br>最后轮到那些选择战斗或射击的人。<br><br>游戏主持人按顺序查看此列表，玩家和反派在行动轮依次响应。例如，主持人大致知道玩家的计划，所以从头开始。“好的，这一轮有谁想说话吗？”想对反派大喊、试图阻止他们的玩家就举手。在这些玩家行动后，主持人询问下一批玩家：“这一轮结束了，有人要到处跑吗？”等等。<br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i> </i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">Now you know what everyone wants to do on both sides, the big question is who gets to go first and who does what? Each character can only take one action at a time, and they’ll get to act in the order below, which depends on the type of action they take.<br><br><strong>Talkers:</strong> “No, no, no... wait!” <br>Talking, or shouting, has proved to be very important in the Doctor’s adventures, words being far more powerful (and usually quicker to use) than weapons. The place can be exploding or you could be held at gunpoint, but before anyone starts shooting or tying you up, you get to say your piece.<br><br><strong>Movers:</strong> “When I say run, run! RUN!” <br>Running is a frequent option, and often when facing an alien threat people start a round running. They could be running away from something or just running into the location, but they’re on the move so they get to go next. Even if you’re sneaking into the secret base as quietly as possible, trying to avoid security cameras, you’re moving from one place to the next, so you’re next in the pecking order.<br><br><strong>Doers:</strong> “I’ve just got to reverse the polarity of this circuit, and we’ll be fine!” <br>It can be as intricate as rewiring a circuit, or it could be as simple as opening a door. If you’re not running or talking to the enemy, you’re probably planning on doing something that’ll help the situation.<br><br><strong>Fighters:</strong> “Open Fire! All Weapons!” <br>Finally, the people who choose to fight or shoot take their turn.<br><br>The Gamemaster goes through this list in order, and the players and villains take their turn when it’s their part of the action round. For example, the Gamemaster roughly knows what the players have planned, so starts from the top. “OK, any characters want to do any Talking this round?” Any players intending on shouting at the villains to try to stop them hold up their hands. After those players have gone, the Gamemaster calls for the next lot: “Now that’s done, anyone planning on just running around?” And so on.</div></div></div><br><span style="color: purple;" class="bbc_color"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" class="bbc_size"><strong>CHARACTERS ROLL AND PERFORM THEIR ACTIONS<br>角色掷骰与行动</strong></span></span><br><br>当角色轮到自己的行动回合时，就是时候让他们按意愿行动了。很多情况下，对手会以某种方式抵抗他们的行动，比如争吵、虚张声势、拳打脚踢、开枪或试图施加精神控制。而如果角色们做一些无需抵抗的事，比如跑动、修理电脑、拆除炸弹，或者目标完全没有发现角色的突袭，那么只需简单地设置难度值掷骰一次。如果有人抵抗角色的行为，将会有一个“反应”判定来决定玩家的行动有多难。<br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i> </i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">When it’s their turn to go in the action round, it’s time for the characters to do their thing. In many cases, their opponent will resist the intended action in some way, whether this is arguing, bluffing, punching, shooting or trying to mentally control someone. Other times it will be a simple roll against the Difficulty of their action, if they are doing something with no resistance, such as running, fixing a computer, defusing a bomb or if the target is completely unaware of the first attack. If someone resists the character’s actions, there will be a ‘Reaction’ to determine how hard it is for the player to act.</div></div></div><br><span style="color: purple;" class="bbc_color"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" class="bbc_size"><strong>REACTIONS – RESISTING THE ROLL<br>反应——抵抗掷骰</strong></span></span><br><br>在冲突中，角色面对对手的行动试图自卫。无论是格挡剑击，躲避戴立克的火力，还是据理力争以阻止战争委员会犯下可怕错误，这些防御行动都是反应。<br><br>这和对抗掷骰方式一样(见77页)。一个角色声明自己的行动，受“攻击”的另一个角色有机会做出反应。防御方优先反应，为攻击者设置难度值，就像普通的掷骰一样。然而，只有当角色意识到对手即将采取行动时，才能够作出反应。<br><br>侧边栏是关于示例行动和对其反应的建议。这些只是可能的组合的一小部分，根据情况变化，游戏中可能会使用完全不同的技能和属性。<br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i> </i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">During a Conflict, the character will want to defend themselves from an adversary’s action. Whether this is parrying a sword, dodging Dalek weapon fire or countering an argument to stop a war committee from making a terrible mistake, these defending actions are Reactions.<br><br>This works in the same way as any other Contested Roll (see pg.77). The character declares their intended action, and the character they are “attacking” has a chance to make a Reaction. The defending character makes their Reaction first, setting the Difficulty for the attacker, just like a normal roll. Reactions should only be allowed, however, if the character is aware of the opponent’s impending action.<br><br>The sidebar suggests some sample actions and reactions. These represent only a small sample of possible combinations, and depending upon the circumstances entirely different skills and attributes may come into play.</div></div></div><table class="bbc_table"><tr><td><span style="color: orange;" class="bbc_color"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt;" class="bbc_size">EXAMPLE REACTIONS<br>反应示例</span></strong></span></tr><tr><td><span style="color: orange;" class="bbc_color"><strong>ACTION<br>行动</strong></span><td><strong><span style="color: orange;" class="bbc_color">REACTION<br>反应</span></strong></tr><tr><td><strong>Arguing<br>争辩</strong><td>Resolve + Convince<br>决心+说服</tr><tr><td><strong>Seduce<br>引诱</strong><td>Resolve + Ingenuity<br>决心+才智</tr><tr><td><strong>Brawling<br>打斗</strong><td>Coordination + Fighting (dodge)<br>or Strength + Fighting (block)<br>协调+战斗（闪避）或力量+战斗（格挡）</tr><tr><td><strong>Gunfire<br>开火</strong><td>Awareness + Coordination (dive for cover)<br>感知+协调（卧倒躲避）</tr><tr><td><strong>Sneaking<br>潜行</strong><td>Awareness + Subterfuge<br>感知+诡计</tr></table></div>
</div>
</div>
