<div class="post">
<div class="inner" id="msg_1129486"><strong><span style="color: purple;" class="bbc_color"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" class="bbc_size">MAKING MORE THAN ONE ACTION IN A ROUND<br>一轮中多次行动</span></span></strong><br><br>无论是跑动、对话、行动还是战斗，你在一轮中只能进行一个动作，但依然可能成为不止一个冲突的目标。反抗理论上该算作一次反应，但一心多用必然带来困难。你的第一次动作正常判定，但之后采取的每个行动，比如射击或喊叫，都会受到-2惩罚。惩罚是累积的，所以之后的每一个额外行动都会追加-2!<br><br><strong>示例：</strong>在与博士一起抢劫时，Psi从一个Dalek那里逃跑，Dalek显然还没意识到他想盗窃飞碟的数据库。他希望凭意识黑入飞碟的电脑，以关上身后的隔板。他的第一个动作是入侵电脑，这算作一次“行动”，正常掷骰。然而，他却遭到了戴立克的射击。它开火了，Psi卧倒躲开，但因为他这一轮已经行动过了，所以反应受到-2惩罚。如果Psi还想做别的事，就要受-4惩罚。<br><br>你可以主动要求在一个行动轮中做不止一件事，但是，第一次之后的每个行动都要累加-2点数。<br><br>而反应的机制则稍有不同。<br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i> </i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">You only get one action in a round, whether it’s running, talking, doing or fighting, but that doesn’t mean that you won’t be targeted by more than one Conflict. Resisting is technically a Reaction, but you can’t do more than one thing at a time without things getting difficult. You get your action as normal, but every other different action you take in the sequence, such as shooting or shouting, receives a -2 penalty. This penalty is cumulative as well, so each additional action after that gets another -2 on top!<br><br><em><strong>Example: </strong>On a heist with the Doctor, Psi is running away from a Dalek apparently unimpressed by his theft of the saucer’s data-vault. He’s hoping to hack into the saucer’s computer with his mind to close a bulkhead behind him. His first action is going be hacking into the computer as that’s a ‘Doing’. He rolls as normal. However, he’s getting shot at by the Dalek. It fires, and Psi dives out of the way, but as he’s already acted this round, this Reaction receives a -2 penalty. If Psi wants to do anything else it’ll be at a -4 penalty.</em><br><br>You can voluntarily do more than one thing in a Round, but again, every action after the first is at a cumulative -2 to the roll.<br><br>Reacting works a little differently.</div></div></div><br><span style="color: purple;" class="bbc_color"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" class="bbc_size"><strong>MAKING MORE THAN ONE REACTION IN A ROUND<br>一轮中多次反应</strong></span></span><br><br>你可以在一轮中多次作出反应，但多数情况下你不必这么做。一旦你跳来跳去进行躲闪，那么每个向你射击的人就都更难击中你——你不需要分开躲避每一次射击。如果你必须在一个回合中做出反应，正常掷骰（并算上任何必要的惩罚值）。这一次掷骰适用于本轮所有对你发起的相似的攻击。<br><br>假设博士被三个志留人瞄准射击，而他在调整音速起子的设置以击毁对手的枪。“行动”的顺序靠前，所以设置音速起子是正常掷骰。接下来是战斗。博士的音速起子要到下一轮才能使用，所以轮到三个志留人开火。他决定躲闪，跳来跳去寻找掩护。博士已经行动过了（调整音速起子），所以他的闪避动作受-2惩罚。他只需要掷一次骰，得出的结果为攻击他的三个志留人设定了同样的目标。<br><br>如果志留人首领试图在这一轮抢先命令博士投降，那么由于“对话者”优先行动，所以博士会在调整音速起子之前先进行抵抗。他对劝降的抵抗是正常掷骰（并且同样用于对抗其他所有人的劝降）。接下来设置音速起子受-2惩罚。然后躲避总共的三次射击受-4惩罚。<br><br>一次掷骰用于多次抵抗，这只适用于反应，而不适用于行动。<br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i> </i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">You can make more than one Reaction roll in a round, but in many cases you don’t actually need to. Once you’re leaping around and dodging, you’re harder to hit for everyone who’s shooting at you – you don’t need to try to dodge every single shot. If you have to react in a round, roll as normal (with any necessary penalties for when you make the roll). That Reaction roll counts for every similar attempt against you in that round.<br><br>Let’s say the Doctor is being shot at by three Silurians while he’s trying to adjust the settings on his Sonic Screwdriver to knock out their guns. The ‘Doing’ comes first, so setting the Sonic Screwdriver is rolled as normal. Then comes the fighting. The Doctor’s Sonic Screwdriver isn’t going to be ready to use until next round so the three Silurians open fire. He’s going to dodge, jumping for cover. The Doctor’s already acted this time (adjusting the Sonic Screwdriver) so his dodging is at -2. He only needs to roll once, and that result sets the target for all three of the Silurians trying to hit him.<br><br>If the Silurian’s leader was trying to command him to surrender earlier in the round, ‘Talkers’ come first, so he would resist that before trying to adjust the Sonic Screwdriver. His resistance against being talked into surrendering would be rolled as normal (and would count against any other attempts to talk him out of what he’s doing). Setting the Sonic Screwdriver would be next in the round, with a -2 penalty. Then the dodge against all three shots would be rolled at -4.<br><br>Using the same roll for multiple resistances only works with Reactions, not with actions.</div></div></div><br><span style="color: orange;" class="bbc_color"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" class="bbc_size"><strong>MITIGATING CIRCUMSTANCES<br>缓和状况</strong></span></span><br><br>虽然有这些规则，某些条件下游戏主持人依然有权决定实际情况。例如，如果你已经在跑动了，此时开始一个行动轮，主持人可能会交换对话者和移动者的顺序。移动者忙着跑来跑去，所以他们飞速掠过对话者身边时，后者不会有多少机会对他们大喊大叫。主持人决定特殊情况是否会让角色按照新的顺序行动。<br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i> </i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">As with any of these rules, there can be times when the Gamemaster may have to decide the actual events. For example, if you start an action round while you’re already running, the Gamemaster may swap the order of the Talkers and the Movers. They’re already running, so the Talkers aren’t going to get much of a chance to shout at you as you breeze past them. The Gamemaster will decide if special circumstances mean that characters go in a different order.</div></div></div><br><span style="color: orange;" class="bbc_color"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" class="bbc_size"><strong>CHANGING YOUR MIND?<br>改变主意？</strong></span></span><br><br>如果玩家临时变卦决定执行一个属于较早阶段的动作，并且还没有行动，他们可以立即开始。这通常是因为他们可能已经为这一轮做了计划，但在他们有机会采取行动之前问题就解决了。<br><br><strong>示例：</strong>凯特·斯图尔特正准备向外星赏金猎人——残暴者维楚斯开枪，但维楚斯早一步行动，激活了他的力场。凯特知道对着力场开枪是没用的，这会毫无效果。她改变了主意，决定跑开寻求帮助——但移动者的回合已经过了！<br><br>凯特的玩家汤姆打断进程，宣布了他想做的事情，而游戏主持人彼得允许凯特在其他人开始进一步的行动和战斗动作之前跑走寻求帮助。如果玩家要求掷骰，主持人可以施加-2的惩罚，以表现出角色在最后关头改变主意并且准备不足的情形。<br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i> </i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">If a player decides that they want to perform an action belonging to an earlier phase, and have not acted yet, they can jump in straight away. This is usually because they may have had something planned for the round, but it was resolved before they had an opportunity to act.<br><br><em><strong>Example:</strong> Kate Stewart is planning to shoot at a Vitrus the Cruel, an alien bounty hunter, but Virtus acted earlier, activating his forcefield. Kate knows that shooting at the forcefield is going to be pointless as her gun will have little effect. She changes her mind, and decides to run for help – however the Movers phase has already passed!<br><br>Kate’s player, Tom, jumps in and declares what he wants to do, and the Gamemaster, Peter, lets Kate run for assistance before any further Doing or Fighting actions take place. The Gamemaster may apply a -2 penalty to any actions like this if they require a roll to reflect the character changing their mind at the last minute and being unprepared.</em></div></div></div><br><span style="color: orange;" class="bbc_color"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" class="bbc_size"><strong>ACTING SIMULTANEOUSLY<br>同时行动</strong></span></span><br><br>如果两个人在同一时间试图做同一件事会怎么样？如果有两个或更多的人想战斗或逃跑，那么角色就按照所使用的最高属性排行动顺序。例如，如果两个人打算互相射击，则协调度更高的人先开枪。如果他们属性值相等，那么技能值高的优先。如果各方面都一样，那么他们的行动就是同时发生的！<br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i> </i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">What if two people are trying to do the same thing at the same time? If two or more people are intending to Fight or to Run then the characters go in order of the highest attribute used. For example, if two people plan on shooting at each other, the one with the highest Coordination goes first. If they both have the same level attribute, then the highest skill goes first. If they are alike in every way, their actions are simultaneous!</div></div></div><br><span style="color: orange;" class="bbc_color"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" class="bbc_size"><strong>EXTENDED CONFLICT SUMMARY<br>扩展冲突总结</strong></span></span><br><br>听起来太复杂了？别担心，一步一步来：<br><br><span style="color: orange;" class="bbc_color"><strong>1）建立场景</strong></span><br>每个人站在哪里？环境是什么样的？<br><span style="color: orange;" class="bbc_color"><strong>2）建立意图</strong></span><br>每个人打算做什么？NPC们又打算做什么？<br><span style="color: orange;" class="bbc_color"><strong>3)采取行动</strong></span><br>每个人（包括NPC）按行动类型决定顺序:<br><strong>对话者</strong>——想要说话的人先开口。<br><strong>移动者</strong>——移动或跑动的人是下一个。<br><strong>行动者</strong>——非战斗的动作，比如修理东西或做其他事。<br><strong>战士</strong>——最后轮到战斗动作。<br>直接针对角色或NPC的行动在发生时可以用反应来抵抗。<br><span style="color: orange;" class="bbc_color"><strong>4）再来一遍</strong></span><br>如果冲突还没解决，回到第二步，继续决定接下来每个人做什么。<br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i> </i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">Sound too complicated? Don’t worry, just take it one stage at a time:<br><br><span style="color: orange;" class="bbc_color"><strong>1) Establish the Scene</strong></span><br>Where is everyone and what is the environment like?<br><span style="color: orange;" class="bbc_color"><strong>2) Establish Intent</strong></span><br>What is everyone planning to do? What are the NPCs planning to do?<br><span style="color: orange;" class="bbc_color"><strong>3) Take Actions</strong></span><br>Everyone gets their action (including the NPCs) in order of what they’re planning to do:<br><strong>Talkers</strong> – any people who are just going to speak, they go first.<br><strong>Movers</strong> – people who are moving or running, they go next.<br><strong>Doers</strong> – non-combat actions, such as fixing something, or doing something.<br><strong>Fighters</strong> – finally, the combat actions go last.<br><span style="color: orange;" class="bbc_color"><strong>4) Do it all again</strong></span><br>If the Conflict hasn’t been resolved, go back to Step 2 and decide what everyone intends to do next.<br></div></div></div><br><span style="color: purple;" class="bbc_color"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" class="bbc_size"><strong>DO IT ALL AGAIN...<br>再来一遍</strong></span></span><br><br>当每个人都行动过了——对话者，移动者，行动者和战士，你可以重新开始这个过程。回到建立意图阶段，讨论你们的角色要做什么——然后完成新一个行动轮。持续反复，直到冲突解决，然后继续接下来的冒险。<br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i> </i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">When everyone has had their action, and you’ve worked your way through the talkers, movers, doers and fighters, you can start the process again. Return to the Establish Intent phase when you’re discussing what your characters are all going to do – then run through another action round. This continues until the Conflict is resolved and you progress on to the rest of the adventure.</div></div></div><br><strong><span style="color: orange;" class="bbc_color"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" class="bbc_size">边栏：</span></span></strong><br>将冲突分解成回合，特别是在战斗中这么做，会有个麻烦：玩家有时会陷入套路，一遍又一遍地重复同样的行动。这不仅使故事冗长无趣，而且聪明的敌人最终会找到方法对抗这种可预测的战术。<br><br>在一个场景中，如果玩家使用相同的策略或行动对付敌人达到三轮，游戏主持人应该开始给敌人累积的+1加值来抵抗。 接下来的每一轮，角色如果再次使用相同的策略或行动，也是如此（加值上限等于敌人的才智）。<br><br><strong>示例：</strong>博士使用说服，让戴立克们相信手里的饼干是TARDIS自毁装置，从而使它们陷入困境。当他第三次这么做时，戴立克得到+1加值来抵抗他的说服企图，并且之后每一轮都额外+1（最高到+4，这与它们的才智相等），直到战略家戴立克识破了诡计。<br><br>“好吧，这其实是Jammy Dodger！可是人家答应给我茶喝！”<br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i> </i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">A problem with breaking Conflicts into shorter rounds, especially combat, is that players can sometimes get stuck in a rut, repeating the same action over and over again. Besides being a colossal bore storywise, any intelligent enemy will eventually figure a way to counter such predictable tactics.<br><br>If the players have used the same tactic or action against the enemy for three rounds in a single scene, the Gamemaster should start giving the enemy a cumulative +1 bonus to resist for that and every additional round that the characters uses the same tactic or action again (to a maximum equal to the enemy’s Ingenuity).<br><br><em><strong>Example:</strong> The Doctor is holding the Daleks at bay with a biscuit by Convincing them that it is a TARDIS self-destruct. The third time he does this, they get a +1 to resist his Convince attempts, and an additional +1 for every round after that (up to +4, which is equal to their Ingenuity) until the Strategist Dalek sees past the ruse.<br><br>“Alright, it’s a Jammy Dodger! But I was promised tea!”</em></div></div></div><br><span style="color: purple;" class="bbc_color"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" class="bbc_size"><strong>LOSING A CONFLICT<br>在冲突中失败</strong></span></span><br><br>失败可能意味着很多事情，这取决于主角卷入的冲突类型。物理冲突，比如战斗，会导致身体受伤甚至死亡。精神冲突，如意志上的斗争或精神控制的尝试，可能会导致他们无法自控，失去意识，或在极少数情况下导致死亡。社交冲突会导致失去威望、尊重甚至他人的信任。<br><br>在很多情况下，在冲突中失败会导致一个或多个角色的属性暂时减少。游戏主持人将与玩家讨论，以确定到底发生了什么以及冲突的结果，从而让失败变得更有趣，强化冒险的动机。<br><br>属性减少的严重程度，甚至角色能否存活，取决于故事点的战略性消耗，以及角色在冲突中失败得有多惨。大多数情况下，你需要知道你被打败得多狠，结果是Failure, Bad, 还是更不幸的Disastrous.<br><br>后文将介绍不同种类的冲突以及怎样处理失败。<br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i> </i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">Losing can mean many things depending upon what sort of Conflict our heroes were engaged in. Physical Conflicts, such as fighting or combat, will result in physical injury or even death. Mental Conflicts, such as a battle of wills or attempts at mind control, may result in losing control of their actions, unconsciousness or on rare occasions, death. Social Conflicts can result in losing prestige, respect or even the trust of others.<br><br>In many cases, losing a Conflict will result in the temporary reduction of one or more of the character’s attributes. The Gamemaster will discuss this with the players to determine exactly what happens and what the outcome of the Conflict is, allowing you to make a failure interesting to heighten the action of the adventure.<br><br>How severe this reduction is, or even the very survival of your character, will depend upon the strategic expenditure of Story Points, and how badly your character lost in the Conflict. In most cases, you’ll need to see how badly you were defeated, whether this is a Failure, a Bad or, even worse, a Disastrous result.<br><br>We’ll go through the various types of Conflict below and discuss how to handle losing.</div></div></div><br><span style="color: purple;" class="bbc_color"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" class="bbc_size"><strong>MAKING LOSING EXCITING<br>让失败更激动人心</strong></span></span><br><br>当然，失败并不总是坏事。凭借想象力，它实际上可以使事情更令人兴奋，让游戏更有趣。失败仍然意味着你输掉了一场冲突，但你依然可以让这成为故事中很酷的一部分。让它变得更有戏剧性、更刺激，会让每个人都觉得冒险很棒，而游戏主持人也会奖励那些运气不佳的玩家，分配故事点以保持游戏的顺利进行。<br><br>失败对故事本身来说也很酷。毕竟，有许多伟大的故事是在冒险的开始出了岔子，然后在余下部分努力纠正错误。无论是被坏人抓住，还是引发了一系列需要解决的灾难性事件，都能造就一个伟大故事。<br><br>如果一个玩家的故事点太少，经主持人同意，玩家可以把成功结果改为失败（或更糟）以推进情节（花费故事点改善结果的反向操作）。这让事情更有趣，也给予玩家必要的故事点，保留到最后让冒险在高潮中结束。当然，主持人拥有最终决定权，通过这种方式获取故事点应该在冒险进程合理的情况下谨慎进行。<br><br><strong>示例：</strong>丹尼•平克成功从Skovox Blitzer 那里逃走，它在一座废弃工厂里追丢了。他本想把它引到博士的陷阱里，但他的逃跑路线堵住了，而且用完了故事点。这里没有信号，所以他无法与博士和克拉拉联系，也不确定他们在哪里。扮演丹尼的玩家英格丽德掷骰以溜过 Blitzer，她成功了，但她决定不让丹尼漫无目的地闲逛，而是决定把结果降级为失败。这让Skovox Blitzer发现了丹尼，推动了情节的发展，同时丹尼仍有时间来避开它的火力。由于把成功变为失败，游戏主持人彼得奖励给英格丽德一个故事点，然后在故事中加入一个新事件。丹尼靠墙站着，屏住呼吸，却撞倒了一堆生锈的管道，引发了Skovox Blitzer的警觉。他有时间逃跑，但声音也吸引了博士的注意，他还在准备陷阱——是时候让它派上用场了！<br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i> </i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">Of course, failing isn’t always bad. It can, with some imagination, actually make things more exciting and the game more interesting. Failures will still mean that you lose a Conflict, but it doesn’t mean that you can’t make this a cool part of the story. Making it more dramatic and exciting makes the adventure more interesting for everyone, and the Gamemaster will reward players who go with their downturn in fortune by awarding the character Story Points for keeping things running smoothly.<br><br>Losing can be really cool for the story as well. After all, how many great stories come from something going wrong at the beginning of an adventure, then spending the rest of the story trying to right the mistake? Whether this is getting captured by villains, or setting in motion a chain of disastrous events that need fixing, it all makes for a great story.<br><br>If a player is running low on Story Points, and if the Gamemaster agrees, the player can opt to adjust a successful roll to a Failure (or worse) to advance the plot (just the reverse of spending Story Points to improve a roll), making things more interesting, and giving the player some Story Points that they can save for the adventure’s climactic finale. Of course, the Gamemaster has the final say on all of this, and gaining Story Points in this way should be done sparingly and when the adventure allows.<br><br><em><strong>Example: </strong>Danny Pink has managed to escape the Skovox Blitzer, losing it in a derelict factory. He was hoping to lead it into the Doctor’s trap, but his escape route is blocked and he’s out of Story Points. There’s no signal here, so he has no way of communicating with the Doctor or Clara and is unsure where they are. His player, Ingrid, rolls to sneak past the Blitzer and succeeds, but instead of wandering around aimlessly, decides to reduce the result to a Failure. This moves the plot along by alerting the Skovox Blitzer to Danny’s presence, but it still gives him time to get out of the way of its weapons fire. The Gamemaster, Peter, rewards Ingrid with a Story Point for reducing her success to a Failure, and then works a new event into the story. As he’s leaning by a wall, catching his breath, Danny knocks over a pile of rusty pipes, alerting the Skovox Blitzer. He has time to make a run for it, but the sound also attracts the Doctor’s attention, who’s still preparing his trap – time to put it into action!</em></div></div></div></div>
</div>
</div>
